Hi, I don't think CheckContinuous function is necessary. here are two reasons:
1. class TBlob seems to be continuous always. because of [CheckContiguous function in TBlob class](https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/14ae5d4ef09ce4334603da9ad32af1f697ad6961/include/mxnet/tensor_blob.h#L170-L172);
2. the inputs (from, to) of TBlob type will convert to Tensor(by `to->FlatTo1D()`) in the primitive implement of ndarray::Copy<cpu,cpu>. accroding to the [code of FlatTo1D](https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/14ae5d4ef09ce4334603da9ad32af1f697ad6961/include/mxnet/tensor_blob.h#L211-L216), [get_with_shape](https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/14ae5d4ef09ce4334603da9ad32af1f697ad6961/include/mxnet/tensor_blob.h#L283-L294),[constructor of tensor](https://github.com/dmlc/mshadow/blob/696803bd7723ade8230af878460d96c68a550fbc/mshadow/tensor.h#L445-L448) and [CheckContiguous function in Tensor](https://github.com/dmlc/mshadow/blob/696803bd7723ade8230af878460d96c68a550fbc/mshadow/tensor.h#L473-L475), when convert TBlob input to Tensor, Tensor's stride_ is assigned by `shape[dim - 1]`, And the `CheckContiguous function` in Tensor always return true. there is no need to check this.

My suggestion to use `register` [here](https://github.com/certbot/certbot/pull/7308#discussion_r313650641) was to define an `AugeasParserNode` _implementation_ so that we weren't duplicating the same `ParserNode` code 3 times and use it without resorting to multiple inheritance. This looks something like:
```
class _AugeasParserNode(interfaces.ParserNode):
    def save():
    ....
class AugeasCommentNode(_AugeasParserNode):
    def __init__():
    ....
AugeasCommentNode.register(interfaces.CommentNode)
```
You could also probably have `_AugeasParserNode` inherit from `object` and register it if you prefer.

As for the interfaces modified in this PR, the three real node interfaces are now defined in a way where to implement the class you do not need to defined the `ParserNode` methods which seems like a problem that should be fixed to me instead of making implementations explicitly register themselves with multiple interfaces. I don't think we ever want a `CommentNode` that is not a `ParserNode`.

I think continuing to use inheritance between the interfaces and fixing the `pylint` issue which is a [known bug in `pylint`](https://github.com/PyCQA/pylint/issues/179) is the best approach.

