I would say that this sequence of events does not look natural to me, in terms of expressing what happens in #1438.

I believe the main event that should be modeled here is "the client disconnects once they have received the response body" - that means, `disconnected` should be set in `send_gen` once the last `http.response.body` has been sent. (Whereas `receive` blocks when it has no available message to send)

```suggestion
    async def recv_gen() -> AsyncGenerator[Message, None]:
        yield {"type": "http.request"}
        await disconnected.await()
        while True:
            yield {"type": "http.disconnect"}

    async def send_gen() -> AsyncGenerator[None, Message]:
        msg = yield
        if msg["type"] == "http.response.body" and not msg.get("more_body", False):
            disconnected.set()
```

