@ultrabug I know you wanted an approach based on USR signals, but I've just tested and in practice `-SIGTERM` doesn't just delete pending notifications, but it _also_ resumes notifications. So the comment is a bit misleading, and `-SIGUSR2` is useless waste of cycles when `-SIGTERM` was already issued. 

How do you feel about this snippet?

```python
if self.parent.pause:
    self.parent.py3.command_run("pkill -x -SIGUSR2 dunst")  # resume
else:
    self.parent.py3.command_run("pkill -x -SIGTERM dunst")  # delete all pending notifications and resume
```

