These five functions are very nearly identical, suggest factoring out the part that is the same into a decorator, something like (untested):
```
def prepare_result(func)
    def wrapper(response, obj, response_headers):
         if obj.errors:
             combined = obj.documents + obj.errors
             results = order_results(response, combined)
         else:
             results = obj.documents
  
         for idx, elt in enumerate(results):
             if hasattr(elt, "error"):
                 results[idx] = DocumentError(id=elt, error=elt)
             else:
                 results[idx] = func(elt)
         return results
    return wrapper
``` 
