Enums should usually end with a "num" parameter, like

```c++
enum Lib {
    cpu_kernels,
    cuda_kernels,
    num_libs
};
```

It helps in cases when you might need to write a for loop over all the enums, though I can't think of any reason why one would want to do that with these. It also lets all of the real options end with commas so they're more easily reordered.

